article.linkText: Stevens' 18 lead Colorado State past Utah State 75-55
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- — Isaiah Stevens' 18 points helped Colorado State defeat Utah State 75-55 on Saturday night. Stevens had eight assists for the Rams (20-6, 8-5 Mountain West Conference). Joel Scott scored 17 points while shooting 7 of 9 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line, and added eight rebounds. Nique Clifford was 4-of-10 shooting (0 for 5 from 3-point range) to finish with eight points, while adding 10 rebounds. Great Osobor led the Aggies (21-5, 9-4) in scoring, finishing with 15 points, 13 rebounds and two steals. Ian Martinez added 14 points for Utah State. In addition, Javon Jackson had 10 points. Colorado State built a 43-26 halftime lead, with Scott racking up 14 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
